(47, 22, 37, 2, 0, '199.116.102.191', 1412384785, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Re: Spoilers Are Broken', '[quote=&quot;Le pug&quot;:1aa3kylv][quote=&quot;DJTiKi&quot;:1aa3kylv]Well that is basically it. If you try to open a spoiler, it just opens and closes the first spoiler in the post. So Spoiler A opens and closes Spoiler A, but Spoiler B,C,D,E and F will open [b:1aa3kylv]and[/b:1aa3kylv] only open Spoiler A.[/quote:1aa3kylv]\n\nYeah I discovered that myself when I looked inside of your thread. I''ll get on it now and try and fix it. Thanks for letting me know. I''ll reply when I have fixed it.[/quote:1aa3kylv]\n\n[spoiler:1aa3kylv]It works![/spoiler:1aa3kylv]\nAnd we have a solution! You can now use a fancy new spoiler tag that allows multiple spoilers to be open. Alongside that, we now have another spoiler tag that isn''t on the BBCode list at the moment:\n\n[code:1aa3kylv]&#91;spoiler=Your Text Here&#93;Hello&#91;/spoiler&#93;[/code:1aa3kylv]\n\n[spoiler=Your Text Here:1aa3kylv]Hello[/spoiler:1aa3kylv]\n\nSo the above shows you how you can actually change the Spoiler! text next to the [+]. Glad to have helped.', 'f0644b20e4586b93b4cd3260dd4b5e23', 0, 'wIAQACA=', '1aa3kylv', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0),
