(58, 33, 30, 2, 0, '199.116.102.191', 1412406434, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Emerald Specials', 'As the thread title says, this thread is about the Emerald specials. The Emerald specials are much less documented than the ones in Fire Red so the purpose of this thread is to get more information on them.\n\n[quote=&quot;Shiny Quagsire&quot;:22jb4nxf]I think the best way to go about some of these commands would be direct reverse engineering. Also, it should be noted that using special_2 some specials can return a value to a specified variable, which is also important to be documented. As such, here''s some of my small contributions:\n\nThe special table in Emerald is 0x20E entries long, with each function being located in the table at [b:22jb4nxf]081DBA64[/b:22jb4nxf].\nIf these offsets could be futher confirmed as to what they do, either by means of looking at every used special thus far or further research, that would be nice.[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n\nHere is a few lists of specials:\n\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][quote:22jb4nxf]0x12E - not sure, but clicking once will do a sound warp to blackness but if you continuously click on the script it&#39;ll warp you to map 0.0 in the center location &#40;X,Y&#41;\n0x8 - takes you to a secret base with a guy in it. Can warp back to original position.\n0x9 - warps you to warp 0 on map 0.0\n0xA - same as 0x9\n0xD - deletes everything on your computer. Nah, jk. Idk what it does\n0xE - brings up menu &quot;Decorate, Put Away, Toss, Cancel&quot;\n0xF - message &quot;There is no registry&quot; then brings up menu &quot;Decorate, Pack Up, Cancel&quot;\n0x18 - teleports you to X1, Y3 of the current map\n0x1A - PC shut off sound and tile is set to something else\n0x1B - &quot;Please Wait ... ... B Button: Cancel Mixing Records...&quot; followed by twinkling sound and the Mixing Records textbox doesn&#39;t go away. Kind of cool though cus you walk around with the message box up and if you go to a new location, it moves up and down with the sign in the top left corner telling you where you are.\n0x1D - locks player in place &#40;aka lock command&#41;\n0x1E - unlocks player in place &#40;aka release command&#41;\n0x21 - &quot;Please Wait ... ... B Button: Cancel&quot; then battle with a level 4 Poochyena ... maybe saving the professor? Anyways, it&#39;ll save your progress then give you a communication error. epic troll special.\n0x22 - &quot;Please Wait ... ... B Button: Cancel&quot; then message pops up after fade out saying &quot;Communication standby ... please wait&quot; then communication error\n0x24 - brings up player info and Would you like to save? message. without a lock in your script, you can walk around with the message up.\n0x27 - voodoo ritual where clones of you appear in a circle staring at each other.. usually one of them has a palette error\n0x29 - deletes all pokemon in party unless its storing it to be retrieved by some variable or special \n0x30 - turns all hidden sprites into soil sprite &#40;sprite #60&#41;\n0x3A - same as #raw 0x56 aka it pops up a ! emote box above the player&#39;s head\nspecial 0x9B &lt;-- actual riding animation &#40;cable car&#41; \nspecial 0x9A &lt;----- optional. it&#39;s the player warp to the top of the cave. Pretty much only way the effect will look good... unless you&#39;re just gonna edit 0x9B for graphics \n1c7 and 1BE [url=http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/wgrxJ&#46;jpg:22jb4nxf]Click here[/url:22jb4nxf]\n[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n\n[quote=&quot;Dark Sneasel&quot;:22jb4nxf]\n0x3- warp from where you came from\n0x8- want to make your secret base here?\n0x9- Petalburg Pokemon center, door opens\n0xE- Secret base stuff, decorate, put away, etc\n0xF- there is no registry\n0x18-warps you\n0x1B-mixing records\n0x21-Results are different. This was one of them: [url:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/hl9mq&#46;jpg[/url:22jb4nxf] and after the battle you save the game.\n0x22-communication\n0x24-Save game box. Stays in the screen unless waitstate is used.\n0x2A-Choose pokemon for something.\n0x2B-Screen goes black, music gets very corrupted.\n0x2F-Choose from the berry section of the bag.\n0x3A-! over player and faces down\n0x3B-A battle theme seems to start playing. \n0x3E-Battle last battled pokemon/trainer.\n0x3F-Withdraw Pokemon, deposit, etc.\n0x5F-Music seems to get corrupted.\n0x60-Save, glitchy if no save state\n0x61-Sprite changes to the berry watering one. Doesn&#39;t work without waitstate.\n0x62-Trainer profile\n0x63-Seems to say what you last said in the trainer profile. Doesn&#39;t work without waitstate.\n0x6A-Weird noise, and says &quot;SHAKE IT DO THE DIET DANCE&quot;\n0x6F-Tells me the story of a trainer with a glitchy name.\n0x70- <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://i.snag.gy/XAEeM.jpg">http://i.snag.gy/XAEeM.jpg</a><!-- m -->\n0x74-Shows me a list of decorations.\n0x78-A bunch of secret base choices and how many you have.\n0x8D-Screen goes black\n0x90-[s:22jb4nxf]Says &quot;Badges&quot;[/s:22jb4nxf] Says the last message that has been said.\n0x9D-Cable car.\n0x9D-Set the clock\n0x9E-See the clock\n0x9F-Starter choosing bag scene.\n0xA0-Wally scene\n0xA1-Nickname\n0xA2-Shows your party\n0xA4-Berry blender\n0xA5-Tells me I don&#39;t have enough coins, shows coins. \n0xB2-The Gabby and Ty TV stuff.\n0xBF-Choose a pokemon, then get the choices summary, and store.\n0xC0- <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://i.snag.gy/i0HiF.jpg">http://i.snag.gy/i0HiF.jpg</a><!-- m -->\n0xC5-Egg hatch of the first Pokemon in your party. If it&#39;s not an egg it hatches anyways and it becomes level 5 and if it is, it actually hatches.\n0xC7- <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://i.snag.gy/DbIyQ.jpg">http://i.snag.gy/DbIyQ.jpg</a><!-- m -->\n0xCB-After a few secs it puts you in front of player&#39;s house\n0xD0 - starts the safari. setvar 0x40A4 0x2 is needed as the next command for it to work. &#40;for safari menu, setflag 0x88C&#41; more info [url=http&#58;//wahackforo&#46;com/t-10516/gba-scripting-manipulando-safari:22jb4nxf]click here[/url:22jb4nxf]\n0xD1 - ends the safari.\n0xD3-Opens this [url:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/imkep&#46;jpg[/url:22jb4nxf] &#40;pokeblock case&#41;\n0xD8-Tells me to go to grassy areas and look more carefully. Most likely from the Birch script.\n0xD9-PC animation\n0xDA-Animation reverses?\n0xDE-Choose pokemon, shows NOT ABLE for mine\n0xDF-Show&#39;s your first pokemon&#39;s moves screen\n0xE3-Move relearner\n0xF1-battle factory switching\n0xEF-[s:22jb4nxf]battle tent battle with &quot;School Kid KEITH&quot;[/s:22jb4nxf] after testing with Shiny Quagsire, it was discovered that you must put a var before it. Here is what happens with the vars/\n[spoiler]setvar 0x8004 0x?\nspecial 0xEF\n0x0 normal\n0x1 last trainer you battled, flees when you&#39;re gonna lose\n0x2 freezes game\n0x3 he seems to have a fainted team\n0x4 the battle facililty with the old guy\n0x5 battle arena\n0x8 steven battle\n0x9 double battle, he flees when you&#39;re about to lose\n0xF4-Silences the music\n0xF8-Choosing pokemon screen, however you can&#39;t choose any\n0xFB-Deletes party\n0xFC-Player&#39;s computer\n0xFD-Very glitchy PC\n0xFE-Show&#39;s region map\n0x101-Trade, trades with last pokemon you saw, can be fainted though\n0x106-Berry blender maximum speed records\n0x109-someone&#39;s PC, player&#39;s PC, log off\n0x10A-hall of fame, corrupted if you haven&#39;t beaten E4\n0x10B-Diploma for completing pokedex\n0x111- <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://i.snag.gy/S9gs1.jpg">http://i.snag.gy/S9gs1.jpg</a><!-- m -->\n0x112-takes you to boot screen, probably from battle frontier saving and quiting\n0x113-credits\n0x114-little earthquake, messes up a few tiles\n0x116-camera doesn&#39;t follow\n0x117-makes camera follow player\n0x11C-screen goes red, starts shaking\n0x12E-same as 0x3\n0x133-big earthquake\n0x134-now in floor\n0x139-wild battle with last seen pokemon\n0x13A-same but cool kyogre thing before battling\n0x13b-same but diff. image\n0x13d-small earthquake\n0x13f- <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/jakaalhn6ibvf2p/it.AVI">https://www.dropbox.com/s/jakaalhn6ibvf2p/it.AVI</a><!-- m --> &#40;it&#39;s supposed to be once, I spammed&#41;\n0x141-player falls from roof to entrance of mao\n0x142-showpokepic with &#40;?&#41; pokemon doing an animation\n0x145-battle with last pokemon you&#39;ve seen\n0x174-opens bag\n0x17C-answer the lady&#39;s quiz\n0x17D-profile\n0x184-opens bag\n0x186-make a quiz\n0x190-pressing start you can see the player&#39;s name is all nonsense now\n0x191-opens pokeblock case\n0x196-messes up a bunch of tiles\n0x199-shows town name like it would when you walk into it\n0x19A-same as^\n0x19B-a little bit of dust comes from the ceiling during a short earthquake\n0x19D-player moves down a few pixels. can be used more than once and the effects stack until warp\n0x1A0-1A2-communication error\n0x1A3-Wireless communication status, shows how many people are battling, trading and in the union room\n0x1A7-choose something, but none of my pokemon can participate\n0x1AD-Pokemon Jump records\n0x1B0-moves the screen a little bit to the right\n0x1B8-&quot;Battle Tower Single&quot; and a huge box cover most of the screen\n0x1C2-opens battle pyramid bag\n0x1C4-pokemon choosing screen, say&#39;s DON&#39;T HAVE for my pokemon, and once you give them an item it says the item&#39;s name\n0x1CD-shows a small box in the screen with nothing in it\n0x1CF-makes a box that says &quot;Powder&quot; and &quot;0&quot; in the screen. probably for the thing near Fallarbor town\n0x1D6-Groudon and Kyogre fighting\n0x1D7-opens Pokenav\n0x1D8-opens menu like the scientist did to make sure you call Mr.Stone\n0x1DD-teach mega punch, choose pokemon to learn\n0x1E4-a shaking mirrage tower follows you\n0x1E5-fossil falls\n0x1E6-nickname pokemon, but it shows a yellow bulbasaur in the icon\n0x1EA-confetti\n0x1F4-multichoice: Slateport City and exit\n0x1F7-Really tall grass appears\n0x1FC-Same as 0x1D6\n0x1FE-screen does this [url:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/b64L0&#46;jpg[/url:22jb4nxf]\n0x1FF-berry crush pressing speed rankings\n0x201-tell the girl that can&#39;t laugh&#39;s dad the words\n0x20F-takes you to boot screen\n0x210-same as ^\n0x211-player can&#39;t move\n0x212-same as ^\n0x213-0x214-same as ^\n0x215-same as 0x20F[/quote:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\n[quote=&quot;sonic1&quot;:22jb4nxf]Hey, for emerald i have something too:\nSpecials:\n28 - Saves pokemon party into RAM. Used for situations of switching parties (battle frontier)\n29 - Restores that party\n2A - Lets you choose 3 pokemons and puts their party slot in 0x203CEF8\n3B - Plays trainer encounter music (not the battle one) according to the 8015 (trainer number) VAR. Used in the game internal script of trainer spotting.\n91 - Map Refresh. Used in setmaptiles. Similar to FireRed 0x8E.\nAE - WildBattle using Tree wild Data.\nF4 - Stops any music from playing.\nFE - Shows worldmap.\n1F3 - Sets National Dex\n[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n[quote=&quot;Shiny Quagsire&quot;:22jb4nxf]Just based on some initial decompiling, here''s a list of specials that are confirmed to do absolutely nothing:\n[list:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x23 Nothing (bx lr)[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x4E - Puts byte 0x0 at 0203A030[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x5A - Takes a halfword from 020375E4, doubles it, and adds it to the ram location 02039F00, then takes a halfword from the resulting RAM location and stores it at 020375DE[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x65 - Loads a dword from 03005D8C (seems to be a saveblock), adds 0x2e51, then loads a byte from the resulting location and stores it to LASTRESULT.[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x67 - Also loads more stuff from one of the saveblocks[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x68 - More stuff from same saveblock[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x75 - More stuff from same saveblock[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x84 - More stuff from same saveblock, although this one seems to do a bit more with the data it''s reading.[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x92 - Stores value from saveblock at 020375DE[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0xA6 - Saveblock stuffs[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0xB3 - Saveblock stuff, returns only with special 2[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0xB7 - Loads byte at 0202433A and stores it to variable specified in special 2[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0xE5 - Something with vblank callback[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0xF4 - RAM stuffs[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x115 - Absolutely nothing (bx lr)[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x11B Nothing (bx lr)[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x14B - Nothing (bx lr)[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x157 - Stuff with trainer data[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x173 - Stuff with that one saveblock[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x17B - Stuff with that one saveblock[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x17f - Ditto[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x180 - Ditto[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x182 - Ditto[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x183 - Ditto[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x18A - Ditto[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x192-0x194 - Ditto[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x1B4 - Loads byte from 030030FC and stores it to specified variable in special 2[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x1BC - Stores 0x0 at 02039F2A[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x1CC - Loads stuff from trainer saveblock to special 2 variable[/*:m:22jb4nxf]\n[*:22jb4nxf]0x1F0 - Does stuff with trainer block data. Lots of or''ing.[/*:m:22jb4nxf][/list:u:22jb4nxf][/quote:22jb4nxf]\n[b:22jb4nxf]NOTE[/b:22jb4nxf]: Gonna make all of that one list soon.\n\nMore specials discoveries. Quotes are used for a bit of the original script I took it from. I''ll update this as I keep finding more\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0x9B and 0x9A[/b:22jb4nxf]\n[quote:22jb4nxf]setvar 0x8004 0x0\nspecial 0x9B\nspecial 0x9A\nwaitstate\nrelease\nend[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n\nso for setvar 0x8004, if it''s 0x0, player rides UP, if 0x1 player rides, DOWN\nspecial 0x9B is the actual cable car animation\nspecial 0x9A is so the player warps to the new location after the animation\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0xF8[/b:22jb4nxf]\n[quote:22jb4nxf]setvar 0x8005 0x3\nspecial 0xF8[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n\nAs DarkSneasel said: 0xF8-Choosing pokemon screen\nSo this special is used in Battle Frontier in determining how many pokemon you''re bringing in with you. 0x3 means that it''ll check for 3 entries. So then 0x4 means it''ll check for 4 entries, and so on (between 0x1-0x6 of course)\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0x1BE[/b:22jb4nxf]\n[quote:22jb4nxf]special 0x1C7\nsetvar 0x400E 0x0\nsetvar 0x8004 0x9\nsetvar 0x8006 0x0\nspecial 0x1BE\nwaitstate[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n\nSo this is used for menus in the battle frontier. special 0x1BE brings up the menu box, depending on what 0x8004 is. What''s interesting about this though is that some of the vars actually show OWs for pokemon dolls or even images of items on screen without a real menu. One of them even has the lettering change font size? Might need to look into that (0x7) Now for each var number:\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf]setvar 0x8004 0x1\n[img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/XEKWZ&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x2\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/xhW5I&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x3\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/xg2XC&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x4\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/Yjh9c&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x5\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/S8cxC&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x6\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/X2Byp&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x7\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/wzTW9&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x8\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/Un7x0&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0x9\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/n51pH&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0xA\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/Okzw1&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0xB\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/r6zGs&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nsetvar 0x8004 0xC\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/U3n3E&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0xA2[/b:22jb4nxf]\n[quote:22jb4nxf]special 0xA2\nwaitstate\ncompare 0x8004 0xFF\nif 0x5 goto 0x825E7BF\ncompare 0x8004 0xFF\nif 0x1 goto 0x825E943[/quote:22jb4nxf]\nSo this one pops up a pokemon select menu. Choose your pokemon and the if 0x5 statement pretty much continues with the script. the if 0x1 part is if the player chooses the Cancel button on the menu. It''ll go to a another script which can be used as a cancel &quot;Oh you don''t want my help? Bye then&quot; kind of thing.\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0x1B2[/b:22jb4nxf]\n[quote:22jb4nxf]special 0xA2\nwaitstate\nspecial 0x1B2\ncompare 0x8006 0x0\nif 0x1 goto 0x825E8B7\ncompare 0x8006 0x1\nif 0x1 goto 0x825E8C5\ncompare 0x8006 0x2\nif 0x1 goto 0x825E8D3\ncompare 0x8006 0x3\nif 0x1 goto 0x825E8E1\ncompare 0x8006 0x4\nif 0x1 goto 0x825E8EF\ncompare 0x8006 0x5\nif 0x1 goto 0x825E8FD[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n\nSo this one uses the last special we talked about 0xA2 to pull up the menu to choose our pokemon. There''s a little bit more to this script but if you wanna look at it''s entirety go to 0x25E775. The numbers next to var 0x8006 are for which stat it looks at. From what I understand, special 0x1B2 looks up the chosen pokemon''s stats and looks for whichever is highest and the stats are in order I.E. HP is 0x0, Attack is 0x1. About as much as I could get out of it.\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0x1C7 and 0x1BE[/b:22jb4nxf]\n[spoiler:22jb4nxf][img:22jb4nxf]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/wgrxJ&#46;jpg[/img:22jb4nxf][/spoiler:22jb4nxf]\nSpoiler should be good enough info. 1C7 is for BP, 1BE is for description. Goes with setvar 0x8004.\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0x1C9[/b:22jb4nxf]\nThis is the special that is needed in order to remove the BP box from special 0x1C7. For some reason the music goes quiet also.. maybe it''s just me.\n\n[b:22jb4nxf]special 0x1DB[/b:22jb4nxf]\nThis one might need a little more research but as far as I can tell, it removes the boxes off the screen as well, maybe for description box of 0x1BE. Makes the game quiet also.\n\nSo looking at Snizzle4rizzle''s main post, you see that 0x1C7\n\n\n[u:22jb4nxf]special2 events[/u:22jb4nxf]\n[b:22jb4nxf]0x149[/b:22jb4nxf]\n[quote:22jb4nxf]special2 LASTRESULT 0x149\ncompare LASTRESULT 0x19C\nif 0x1 goto @youhaveEggAlready[/quote:22jb4nxf]\n\nso this event is checking if you have an egg in your party if 0x1 then goto script where you have egg', 'ba6dbb72de50513254b73f8ec5213769', 0, '2UAQAg==', '22jb4nxf', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0),
(59, 34, 36, 2, 0, '199.116.102.191', 1412406809, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Tile Insertion For AdvanceMap For Dummies', '[center:pc02v9h1]You can either watch the video or read the tutorial. Your call! I&#39;m here to help in any way possible.\nTo view the old version of this tutorial, scroll to the bottom.\n[hd:pc02v9h1]poH5TQ0hTDI[/hd:pc02v9h1]\n\n\nMore video examples:\nThis is adding a new building:\n [hd:pc02v9h1]WunsZr42LKA[/hd:pc02v9h1]\nThis is adding more tiles to your custom tileset with the new building:\n[hd:pc02v9h1]oAA1p0ldlhs[/hd:pc02v9h1]\nThis one just shows you how quick it can be to add new tiles:\n[hd:pc02v9h1]lGNcNBOv6eY[/hd:pc02v9h1]\nYou can use JUST mspaint, TileHelperAdvance, and AdvanceMap ... but THA isn&#39;t the best at converting to 16 colors, so I recommend using irfanView for that and then using THA afterwards to get the colors to match those required by AMap.\n\nIf you have problems not getting this tutorial to work, COMMENT BELOW. DO NOT VM ME. I will answer shortly.\n\nBackground\n\nWell I&#39;m doing this because I know how hard tutorials can be... I know right? You&#39;d expect tutorials to help but most of the time, at least for me, they confuse me more than anything. So I&#39;m going to share my method of tile insertion. For the longest time I could not do this. I looked at tutorials, videos, talked to people, nothing worked. Finally figured it out, though. And I&#39;m here to help YOU get the tiles you want into your game because if you&#39;re like me, it&#39;s not really worth doing hacks if you can&#39;t spice up the images &#40;though I have to say some hacks pull it off with great stories&#41;.\n\nPrograms You&#39;ll Need \n&#40;or at least what I&#39;m using&#41;\n TileHelperAdvance - [url=https&#58;//www&#46;dropbox&#46;com/s/jv5uzpae2w3wt52/TileHelperAdvance&#46;zip:pc02v9h1]Click here to download[/url:pc02v9h1]\n [b:pc02v9h1]AdvanceMap 1.95[/b:pc02v9h1] &#40;don&#39;t judge me gogojjtech&#41; or if you are like SOME PEOPLE, use 1.92 because 1.95 can be buggy but hey, I have been hacking with BOTH versions &#40;1.92 only version I can import block lists yatta yatta&#41;\n [b:pc02v9h1]msPaint[/b:pc02v9h1] or whatever paint program you want, even photoshop works\n\nExtras You&#39;ll Need\nObviously a rom to insert in and the tiles you want also. There are a lot of public tilesets out there, for a great place to search look on deviantart.\n\nInfo You Want To Know\nFirst of all, my experiences have been with Pokemon Ruby only but I have played with FireRed a bit. This tutorial can be used for all rom types used in AdvanceMap. \n[b:pc02v9h1][u:pc02v9h1]Always back up your rom[/u:pc02v9h1][/b:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/bNDON86&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nAs you can see, I&#39;m [i:pc02v9h1]extra[/i:pc02v9h1] careful. One backup is fine though.. all depends on your preference.\n[b:pc02v9h1]For this tutorial, I&#39;ll be using a Ruby rom. [/b:pc02v9h1]\n\nNmero Uno: Setting Up\nHave a tileset. I will be using a public tileset and you can find it in the spoiler:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//th05&#46;deviantart&#46;net/fs70/PRE/f/2011/088/5/2/latest_tileset_so_far_by_thedeadheroalistair-d27xjkd&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAlright now open AdvanceMap and open your rom. I&#39;ll be using the map PETALBURG CITY &#40;0.0&#41;. Here&#39;s an image of what map if you need it &#40;again this is a tutorial for dummies!&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/G7xfSpO&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow if you go to the header tab in the program &#40;check spoiler for location of Header&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/HlxBQMr&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nthere is something that is important to know! On the bottom of header there is a section called Used tilesets and for PETALBURG CITY, it&#39;s 0 and 1. \n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/UYixsu7&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nNow if you change it from 0 and 1 to 0 and 2 it won&#39;t provide two new tilesets. It&#39;s not like acts and chapters... there are only 58 defaults tilesets in pokemon ruby &#40;0-57&#41;. So if, for example, you change Tileset 1 from 0 to 1... You&#39;ll see in the Map section that it&#39;s the exact same tileset. Combination of numbers again do not change tilesets... but I recommend using 0 as Tileset 1 always because it saves you from buggy looking images like if you used tileset 3 for Tileset 1 and tileset 57 for Tileset 2.. &#40;see how it&#39;d look in the spoiler below&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/IHqPjbl&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nNumber 2: Tile Prepping\nAlright so for the example tiles we are going to use from the tileset I listed earlier, I have chosen the following:\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/pG1c8Cr&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1] \nBut in every tileset there MUST be a transparent color and this color must be different from all the others. I&#39;ve chosen pink since it isn&#39;t in our image. Check below\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/DVPS3Qc&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow you can choose to either get rid of all the tiles from the default tileset or you can start all over... again up to you. For right now, I&#39;m just gonna insert this new water into the tileset to change the water on the PETALBURG CITY map. \n\nSo in AdvanceMap, we&#39;re gonna explore the menu and what we&#39;ll be using. Click on the Block editor &#40;view spoiler to find&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/Ol3rxci&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nNow for a little explanation of the menu buttons. If you already know what they do, skip the below spoiler\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1]Under Picture you have Save Tileset 1, Load Tileset 1, Save Tileset 2, Load Tileset 2, and Load New Blocks. \nSave Tileset 1 and Save Tileset 2 we&#39;ll be using later and pretty much it just saves the tileset image of the current palette wherever you want. \nLoad Tileset 1 and Load Tileset 2 loads images of your desire into the program.\nLoad New Blocks is okay to click whenever you want and usually you use it when you update blocks that are already on the map and you can preview what it&#39;d look like if you changed it without having the forced option of saving what you did if you don&#39;t want to &#40;though it should auto change when you Save the block&#41;. I usually use it when I insert a new tileset that has lots or some changes that I don&#39;t need to do with any blocks.\nUnder Blocks, you have four of the same options which we won&#39;t be dealing with in this tutorial. All you need to know about is 1&#41; Change amount: I use this to get the full benefit of blocks. On default for this tileset 1, it&#39;s 144 and the max is 512. See below:\n[spoiler][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/5asyEzh&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nIt&#39;s up to you to choose how many blocks you want but I always just go max on it and put in 512 lol. See the change below:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/5MTNHmJ&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nyou can see that to the left that big blue spot is just added blocks to use! yay us[/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nDouble Palette view size just doubles the size of the blocks so you can see them better if you&#39;re a blind bat like me. Spoiler for example\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/c4AzzWw&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/A9jyCT9&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nTileset menu item we will not be using\nUnder Palette menu item, we are only going to be using Show Palette Editor.[/spoiler]\n\nNmero Three: Palette Insertion / Image Insertion\n\nAlright so in my previous version of this tutorial, it got a little tricky here. But now life is made simple. Thanks to a simple program: TileHelperAdvance &#40;THA&#41;. You can find the download link above. All you need to do is open your image in THA:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/mNly5&#46;jpg[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nThen you&#39;re going to click the Convert Tileset button. Wait a sec and a message will pop up saying your background color wasn&#39;t black. Don&#39;t worry about this message. The purpose of this program is to get the colors to numbers that the rom can see. So now just click on Save Tileset and save it as whatever. Also click on save palette and select whichever version of advancemap you&#39;re using. if you&#39;re using advancemap 1.95 like, choose that.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/nZMnN&#46;jpg[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow go to your advancemap and find a palette number you wanna use. I&#39;m using palette 6 for this instance. MAKE SURE THE CORRECT PALETTE NUMBER IS CHOSEN BEFORE LOADING PALETTE. If you have pal 0 selected and load your pal 6, then you just lost your pal 0. Anyways, go Block Editor &gt; Palettes &gt; Load palette from file &gt; your file. If done correctly, it shouldve came out to look like:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/L85Ze&#46;jpg[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nNow all you have to do is open your tileset image in mspaint &#40;Picture &gt; save tileset 2 then open it in mspaint&#41;:\n\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/TGnXz&#46;jpg[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nthen open up your newly saved tiles that you saved from THA:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/rJtXP&#46;jpg[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nThen simply drag and drop your tiles from your new image to the tileset that you&#39;re using:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;snag&#46;gy/8xQVB&#46;jpg[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nIf you&#39;ve done this correctly AND you&#39;re using the image I listed earlier, you should get the below spoiler\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/KNTRTtr&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAlright so now go back to your AdvanceMap under the Block editor menu, go to Palette and select Show Palette editor\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/cWue03i&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNote: You can change the palettes of any palette but Palette 12. Palette 12 will not work 100% of the time so don&#39;t use it. Palette 0 is by default used for like PokeMart tile and water tiles, Palette 1 is default for PokeCenter and signs and what not, Palette 2 is default for grass, trees, etc, Palette 3 is default for rocks and mountains, palette 4 is mainly for water tiles and palette 5 is for like sand.\nWith that said unless you&#39;re revamping everything, stay away from palettes 0-5. Palette 6-11 are good for use on all tilesets. \nWe&#39;ll be changing Palette 6 in this example. See below\n\n\nOne thing you should know also, each tileset MUST be 128 x 256 in order to insert it into the rom. \nSo now that your new tile is in place, save the tileset to overwrite it. Now go back into AdvanceMap and go to Picture in the Block editor and click Load Tileset 2 \n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/BVB8xMe&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nand load the tileset image.\nIf you succeeded you should see something like the below image\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/R67HK7g&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nHuzzah! You&#39;ve inserted new tiles. Now I know this is a tile insertion tutorial, but in case you don&#39;t know how to do blocks, I&#39;ll do ONE with you.. I know, I&#39;m generous.\n\nStep Four: Block Creation\nSo you have a ton of new block space to use since you updated the amount of blocks to 512, if you did like I said you should. So choose any like this:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/lVJ6RmZ&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAnd just start adding your new tiles into the Down/Up section. If you add stuff to the Up section, it&#39;d appear above your player and Down will appear below your player unless you use the background byte &quot;Block is covered by hero [10]&quot; anyways click save to update the tile.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/Ob9QzIo&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nSo with that completed, I think you can figure things out from here on out. If you need any help just post here and I or someone will help you. I really hoped this helped you as it did for me. \n\nCredits go to those who created the tiles used in this tutorial and those that I learned from along the way to get to this point. Thanks and enjoy!\n\nFinal Product\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/UjAWahE&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/DQgQ7bs&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1][/center:pc02v9h1]\n\n\nTo see the older version which uses a different method, see below:\n\n[break:pc02v9h1]55[/break:pc02v9h1]\n\n[b:pc02v9h1][u:pc02v9h1][size=200:pc02v9h1][center:pc02v9h1]Alternate Method of Insertion[/center:pc02v9h1][/size:pc02v9h1][/u:pc02v9h1][/b:pc02v9h1]\n\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][center:pc02v9h1]You can either watch the video or read the tutorial. Your call! I&#39;m here to help in any way possible.\n[youtube:pc02v9h1]40A-YOuNfV8[/youtube:pc02v9h1]\n\nBackground\n\nWell I&#39;m doing this because I know how hard tutorials can be... I know right? You&#39;d expect tutorials to help but most of the time, at least for me, they confuse me more than anything. So I&#39;m going to share my method of tile insertion. For the longest time I could not do this. I looked at tutorials, videos, talked to people, nothing worked. Finally figured it out, though. And I&#39;m here to help YOU get the tiles you want into your game because if you&#39;re like me, it&#39;s not really worth doing hacks if you can&#39;t spice up the images &#40;though I have to say some hacks pull it off with great stories&#41;.\n\nPrograms You&#39;ll Need \n&#40;or at least what I&#39;m using&#41;\n [b:pc02v9h1]IrfanView[/b:pc02v9h1] 4.36 &#40;latest version should do&#41;\n [b:pc02v9h1]AdvanceMap 1.95[/b:pc02v9h1] &#40;don&#39;t judge me gogojjtech&#41; or if you are like SOME PEOPLE, use 1.92 because 1.95 can be buggy but hey, I have been hacking with BOTH versions &#40;1.92 only version I can import block lists yatta yatta&#41;\n [b:pc02v9h1]msPaint[/b:pc02v9h1] or whatever paint program you want, even photoshop works\n\nExtras You&#39;ll Need\nObviously a rom to insert in and the tiles you want also. There are a lot of public tilesets out there, for a great place to search look on deviantart.\n\nInfo You Want To Know\nFirst of all, my experiences have been with Pokemon Ruby only but I have played with FireRed a bit. This tutorial can be used for all rom types used in AdvanceMap. \n[b:pc02v9h1][u:pc02v9h1]Always back up your rom[/u:pc02v9h1][/b:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/bNDON86&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nAs you can see, I&#39;m [i:pc02v9h1]extra[/i:pc02v9h1] careful. One backup is fine though.. all depends on your preference.\n[b:pc02v9h1]For this tutorial, I&#39;ll be using a Ruby rom. [/b:pc02v9h1]\n\nNmero Uno: Setting Up\nHave a tileset. I will be using a public tileset and you can find it in the spoiler:\n[spoiler][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//th05&#46;deviantart&#46;net/fs70/PRE/f/2011/088/5/2/latest_tileset_so_far_by_thedeadheroalistair-d27xjkd&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAlright now open AdvanceMap and open your rom. I&#39;ll be using the map PETALBURG CITY &#40;0.0&#41;. Here&#39;s an image of what map if you need it &#40;again this is a tutorial for dummies!&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/G7xfSpO&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow if you go to the header tab in the program &#40;check spoiler for location of Header&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/HlxBQMr&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nthere is something that is important to know! On the bottom of header there is a section called Used tilesets and for PETALBURG CITY, it&#39;s 0 and 1. \n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/UYixsu7&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nNow if you change it from 0 and 1 to 0 and 2 it won&#39;t provide two new tilesets. It&#39;s not like acts and chapters... there are only 58 defaults tilesets in pokemon ruby &#40;0-57&#41;. So if, for example, you change Tileset 1 from 0 to 1... You&#39;ll see in the Map section that it&#39;s the exact same tileset. Combination of numbers again do not change tilesets... but I recommend using 0 as Tileset 1 always because it saves you from buggy looking images like if you used tileset 3 for Tileset 1 and tileset 57 for Tileset 2.. &#40;see how it&#39;d look in the spoiler below&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/IHqPjbl&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nNumber 2: Tile Prepping\nAlright so for the example tiles we are going to use from the tileset I listed earlier, I have chosen the following:\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/pG1c8Cr&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1] \nBut in every tileset there MUST be a transparent color and this color must be different from all the others. I&#39;ve chosen pink since it isn&#39;t in our image. Check below\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/DVPS3Qc&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow you can choose to either get rid of all the tiles from the default tileset or you can start all over... again up to you. For right now, I&#39;m just gonna insert this new water into the tileset to change the water on the PETALBURG CITY map. \n\nSo in AdvanceMap, we&#39;re gonna explore the menu and what we&#39;ll be using. Click on the Block editor &#40;view spoiler to find&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/Ol3rxci&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nNow for a little explanation of the menu buttons. If you already know what they do, skip the below spoiler\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1]Under Picture you have Save Tileset 1, Load Tileset 1, Save Tileset 2, Load Tileset 2, and Load New Blocks. \nSave Tileset 1 and Save Tileset 2 we&#39;ll be using later and pretty much it just saves the tileset image of the current palette wherever you want. \nLoad Tileset 1 and Load Tileset 2 loads images of your desire into the program.\nLoad New Blocks is okay to click whenever you want and usually you use it when you update blocks that are already on the map and you can preview what it&#39;d look like if you changed it without having the forced option of saving what you did if you don&#39;t want to &#40;though it should auto change when you Save the block&#41;. I usually use it when I insert a new tileset that has lots or some changes that I don&#39;t need to do with any blocks.\nUnder Blocks, you have four of the same options which we won&#39;t be dealing with in this tutorial. All you need to know about is 1&#41; Change amount: I use this to get the full benefit of blocks. On default for this tileset 1, it&#39;s 144 and the max is 512. See below:\n[spoiler][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/5asyEzh&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nIt&#39;s up to you to choose how many blocks you want but I always just go max on it and put in 512 lol. See the change below:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/5MTNHmJ&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nyou can see that to the left that big blue spot is just added blocks to use! yay us[/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nDouble Palette view size just doubles the size of the blocks so you can see them better if you&#39;re a blind bat like me. Spoiler for example\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/c4AzzWw&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/A9jyCT9&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nTileset menu item we will not be using\nUnder Palette menu item, we are only going to be using Show Palette Editor.[/spoiler]\n\nSo back to the image... go to irfanView and open your image. Go to Image &gt; Decrease Color Depth &#40;check spoiler if lost&#41;:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/IKUTPY1&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nIn Decrease color depth pop-up, the default is 256 Colors &#40;8 BPP&#41; and you need to change it to 16 Colors &#40;4 BPP&#41; and click the OK button.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/s2fTklt&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow what this did was change the amount of colors in your image from 256 to 16 because the palettes in the game only have 16. Our next step involves some multitasking so pay attention closely! \n\nNmero [s:pc02v9h1]Treeko[/s:pc02v9h1]... err trio... wait that&#39;s not spanish.. oh yeah, Tres: Palette Manipulation\n\nThis part may get tricky but don&#39;t worry, I&#39;m here to hold your hand through it all. \nIn irfanView, go to image &gt; Palette &gt; Edit Palette \n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/PkDRmz0&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nIf you&#39;ve done this correctly AND you&#39;re using the image I listed earlier, you should get the below spoiler\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/KNTRTtr&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAlright so now go back to your AdvanceMap under the Block editor menu, go to Palette and select Show Palette editor\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/cWue03i&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNote: You can change the palettes of any palette but Palette 12. Palette 12 will not work 100% of the time so don&#39;t use it. Palette 0 is by default used for like PokeMart tile and water tiles, Palette 1 is default for PokeCenter and signs and what not, Palette 2 is default for grass, trees, etc, Palette 3 is default for rocks and mountains, palette 4 is mainly for water tiles and palette 5 is for like sand.\nWith that said unless you&#39;re revamping everything, stay away from palettes 0-5. Palette 6-11 are good for use on all tilesets. \nWe&#39;ll be changing Palette 6 in this example. See below\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/26KwWCx&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nIn the above image you see all 16 colors, with the very first color on the top row being the transparent color. This color will always disappear in-game and in advancemap for this particular tileset. What we need to focus on are the RGB numbers &#40;the ones that are in red blue and green text seen in image above&#41;. The numbers are in multiples of 4 so that means we need to do some changes to the palette of the tileset and image. So first we select the first color of the 16 colors in AdvanceMap and our transparent color in irfanView which in my image is the pink.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/Ws3jyqv&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nIn the above image you see that the pink color has the colors Red: 255 Green: 175 Blue: 201\nand the transparent color has Red: 24 Green: 40 and Blue: 80. We need to get the transparent color as close to the pink as possible. So I&#39;ve come up with Red: 248 Blue: 176 Green: 200 &#40;see image below&#41; and once done, you can click the Apply button to change the color permanently.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/9X28TMX&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nSo now we need the RGB numbers to match because if they don&#39;t, your image won&#39;t show up in the tileset and it&#39;ll just be a solid color. So change the palette color in irfanView to the same color as the new transparent color. See below\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/J1Brmjt&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow we just copy all the colors over from irfanView to the palette editor as closely as possible and then change the colors to match in irfanview like we did for the transparent color but for each color now. See below for 3/15 color examples &#40;you can do the rest&#41;\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/BxCEuvD&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/ZuDDxHQ&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/lsE76dX&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAlright so now we should have a finished product:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/kGmcKhy&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAs you can see from above, the palettes match completely. Now we need to save our image in irfanview as a .PNG. \n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/NOkhtkW&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow open that image in msPaint.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/ue9o3U0&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nNow go into AdvanceMap, close out the palette editor and in the same palette you just changed, go to Picture on the menu of Block editor and choose Save Tileset 2 and save it. \n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/w4IYTw4&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nOpen that tileset in a separate msPaint.\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/TTSoFWV&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nnow select your image copy it and paste it into the tileset image in an available space. Now, the blocks are 16x16 with each block having 4 smaller squares which are 8x8. So pretty much just place the image in alignment with the others so that when you create the blocks, the images aren&#39;t off.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/OkvgcxZ&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nOne thing you should know also, each tileset MUST be 128 x 256 in order to insert it into the rom. \nSo now that your new tile is in place, save the tileset to overwrite it. Now go back into AdvanceMap and go to Picture in the Block editor and click Load Tileset 2 \n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/BVB8xMe&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nand load the tileset image.\nIf you succeeded you should see something like the below image\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/R67HK7g&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\nHuzzah! You&#39;ve inserted new tiles. Now I know this is a tile insertion tutorial, but in case you don&#39;t know how to do blocks, I&#39;ll do ONE with you.. I know, I&#39;m generous.\n\nStep Four: Block Creation\nSo you have a ton of new block space to use since you updated the amount of blocks to 512, if you did like I said you should. So choose any like this:\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/lVJ6RmZ&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\nAnd just start adding your new tiles into the Down/Up section. If you add stuff to the Up section, it&#39;d appear above your player and Down will appear below your player unless you use the background byte &quot;Block is covered by hero [10]&quot; anyways click save to update the tile.\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/Ob9QzIo&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1]\n\nSo with that completed, I think you can figure things out from here on out. If you need any help just post here and I or someone will help you. I really hoped this helped you as it did for me. \n\nCredits go to those who created the tiles used in this tutorial and those that I learned from along the way to get to this point. Thanks and enjoy!\n\nFinal Product\n[spoiler:pc02v9h1][img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/UjAWahE&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1]\n[img:pc02v9h1]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/DQgQ7bs&#46;png[/img:pc02v9h1][/spoiler:pc02v9h1][/center:pc02v9h1]', '285ca184124cd78f5b412b3da0783f45', 0, 'fQcwAg==', 'pc02v9h1', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0),
(61, 36, 36, 2, 0, '199.116.102.191', 1412407640, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'How to remove clouds from Emerald titlescreen', '[center:304p9r66][u:304p9r66][b:304p9r66][size=200:304p9r66]How To Remove Clouds From Emerald Titlescreen[/size:304p9r66][/b:304p9r66][/u:304p9r66][/center:304p9r66]For visual stimulation:\n[center:304p9r66][youtube:304p9r66]azrjRQrmTLY[/youtube:304p9r66][/center:304p9r66]\n\nAll you need to do is open up NSE 2.0 and go to Navigate:\n[spoiler:304p9r66][center:304p9r66][img:304p9r66]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/yPbpEaF&#46;png[/img:304p9r66][/center:304p9r66][/spoiler:304p9r66]\n\nType in the offset in the previous image ( 53FC8C ) and click Open. You should see this:\n[spoiler:304p9r66][center:304p9r66][img:304p9r66]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/fVReuRJ&#46;png[/img:304p9r66][/center:304p9r66][/spoiler:304p9r66]\n\nWell simply take the orange color and using the paint tool just draw over the entire image to get it to look like this:\n[spoiler:304p9r66][center:304p9r66][img:304p9r66]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/3fxKulJ&#46;png[/img:304p9r66][/center:304p9r66][/spoiler:304p9r66]\n\nAnd then just click Save:\n[spoiler:304p9r66][center:304p9r66][img:304p9r66]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/5S6Prs4&#46;png[/img:304p9r66][/center:304p9r66][/spoiler:304p9r66]\n\nAnd you''re set! No more clouds.', 'a70e8bf56746b7c15ba3d97ccc248f09', 0, 'TQYQ', '304p9r66', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0);
